<br>
Rains can hit 4 targets in one shot and then stop cuz they reached max target, happened a lot in various rings/aoe groups.<br>
<br>
There is a bigger chance for a mob to resists rains when they reach about 10% of their health, it's a wise thing to switch to DD for that part of the fight. It looks like it's a leftover from the patch they made to prevent mob's corpse poofing. It CAN happen that a rain kills a mob, happened to me on serveral occasion, but it's very very unlikely. Like I said, use DDs for last 10% and works wonders.<br>
<br>
Rains are very powerful, especialy for a class like ours that has access to the best resist debuff in game. Use them, learn them, love them!<br>
<br>
Woon &lt;TDE&gt;<br>
Arch mage, 7th hammer<br>
